The microcontroller is ATmega32U4

To set fuses on new arduino:

    avrdude -c usbasp -p m32u4 -U efuse:w:0xcb:m -U hfuse:w:0xd9:m -U lfuse:w:0xff:m

To check fuses:

    avrdude -c usbasp -p m32u4

==========================================================

If you check it on Gnome desktop, after inserting the device(s) run:

    sudo mmcli --list-modems

Output must be: No modems were found
If it is not, find a way to disable probe. This may help:

    sudo journalctl --unit ModemManager --follow

(or simply run: sudo systemctl stop ModemManager)

==========================================================

Connect USBasp as:

( ) (G) (O) (.) ( ) ( ) ( ) ( ) (B) (G) (V) (.)

(G) = Gray
(O) = Orange
(B) = Brown
(V) = Violet
( ) = no pin
(.) = unused pin

Connect display as:

Display: (1) (2) (3) (4) (5)
Arduino: ( ) (4) (.) (5) ( ) ( ) ( ) ( ) (1) (.) (3) (2)

==========================================================

In ConnectBot add entry to show/hide seconds using this for "run on connect":

    if [ -e /tmp/time.no-seconds ]; then clock seconds; else clock no-seconds; fi; exit
    <empty line>

and enable "close when connection disappears"

For setting brightness analogously add entries using this (N is 0, 1 or 2):

    clock N; exit
    <empty line>

Name each entry in ConnectBot as 0 1 2 [X] (one server) or
c0 c1 c2 [cX] k0 k1 k2 [kX] etc. (many servers).
(X is for show/hide seconds, if this is used)
Use these colors: *0=grey, *1=blue, *2=green, [*X]=red
